The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs and optimization, specifically the Generalized Demand Matching problem. The techniques used involve matroid theory, dynamic programming, and randomized rounding. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.RO (Robotics).
